<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-02-20T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-02-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="910" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5034 Business Tax/2: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-20T17:00:00-05:00">February 20, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>62. Your 71, February 16, 7 p.m. Department approves your February 16, 6
                            p.m. to Hankow.</p>
                        <p>Authorize Hankow to inform the Chairman of the Hupeh Provincial
                            Government that the regulations cannot be considered applicable to
                            American firms.</p>
                        <p>Report developments fully by mail.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>